EnemyDataOrokin.name: Alpine Monitor Sawgaw
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: 'Soar Gore' as the Solaris call it, this crimson-faced bird of prey circles and stalks the cliffs and fungal forests of Venus, searching for rodent prey.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Alpine Monitor Sawgaw

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Amethyst Nexifera
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: A distinctly Deimosian grotesquerie that attacks it opponents from above.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Amethyst Nexifera

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Arbitration Shield Drone
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: The Arbiters of Hexis created this drone to put Tenno to the test in Arbitrations.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Arbitration Shield Drone

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Ashen Kuaka
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: A timid rodent that is easily frightened.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Ashen Kuaka

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Bau Vasca Kavat
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: The Vasca strain is a symbiotic blood-borne virus transmitted via the saliva of infected kavats. Existing solely to propagate itself the virus makes the host increasingly dependent upon the ingestion of blood, thereby spreading itself further and faster through the population. Vasca-infected kavats, over time, lose all sense of themselves becoming increasingly cunning, violent and ravenous.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Bau Vasca Kavat

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Black-Banded Bolarola
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: Favoring thunder, lightning and cratered-out areas Bolarolas are all about defense. Their armored plates protect them from most predators, tucking-and-rolling to make good their escape.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Black-Banded Bolarola

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Brindle Kubrodon
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: The apex predator of the Venusian plains. These massively framed beasts travel in groups and mark the territory surrounding Orokin cooling towers as their own. Kubrodons are a danger best avoided.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Brindle Kubrodon

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Burrowing Cryptilex
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: The most abundant variety of Cryptilex, this aggressive insect will slash anything it deems a threat.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Burrowing Cryptilex

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Caustic Cryptilex
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: The most dangerous Cryptilex. They have glands in their abdomens that can emit an acidic spray.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Caustic Cryptilex

EnemyDataOrokin.Description: Clem Clem
EnemyDataOrokin.Missions: A Man of Few WordsHelp Clem

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Coastal Mergoo
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: An avian of ridiculous appearance found along coastal regions and around large bodies of water. Mergoo circle and squawk at the sight of marine predators. Many an Ostron fisher owes their lives to these odd little birds. Killing one is considered very bad luck.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Coastal Mergoo

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Common Condroc
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: A carrion-eater and opportunistic bird-of-prey. Condrocs gather, feed upon carrion, and occasionally, hunt in groups known as 'committees'. Several committees will be led by an Emperor.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Common Condroc

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Crescent Vulpaphyla
EnemyDataOrokin.Description:
The Crescent is the most pugnacious subspecies of Vulpaphyla, they will rush anything they perceive as a threat.

Active only while Vome watches over the Cambion Drift.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Crescent Vulpaphyla

EnemyDataOrokin.name: Dappled Horrasque
EnemyDataOrokin.Description: Found near bodies of water the Horrasque subsists primarily upon fish. This hideous creature is terrible to behold but will not attack unless provoked. When it does its roar will shake the bowels of even the most steadfast trapper.
EnemyDataOrokin.Name: Dappled Horrasque
